Translate the coordinate system.

The [transform](/documentation/tags/transform.html) methods are used to position
objects in your application. You can translate along a particular axis (x,y,z) or
along an arbitrary axis. See the [examples](#examples) section below
for usage.

{:.alert.alert-info}
Be sure to wrap `translate` calls with `pushMatrix()` and `popMatrix()` to restore
the environment to its original state. Otherwise, all subsequent rendering calls
will be translated as well.

See the [coordinate system tutorial](/tutorials/coordinate-transformations.html)
for more information.

### syntax

~~~ python
translateX(tx)
translateY(ty)
translateZ(tz)
translate(dist, dir)
~~~

### parameters

tx   | amount of translation in the x-axis
ty   | amount of translation in the y-axis
tz   | amount of translation in the z-axis
dist | amount of translation in arbitrary direction
dir  | direction of translation

