#### drawing multiple cubes at random positions

{:.alert.alert-info}
The following code can be simplified by using [batch\_mode](/documentation/utils/batch-mode.html)
rendering. This example is for illustration purposes only.


<%= vroom_example_image "core", "translate", "drawing-multiple-cubes-at-random-positions.png" %>


~~~ python
def init():
   num_cubes = 20
   Global.positions = list(random_vertex_generator(num_cubes, -10.0, 10.0))

def display():
   lighting(False)
   for pos in Global.positions:
      pushMatrix()
      translate(pos)
      cube(3.0)
      popMatrix()
~~~
